textAfterTable: September 8, 2010 - 11:48am -- braswell POPLARVILLE - Pearl River Community College''s Wildcats remain undefeated after Tuesday''s 4-0 home shutout over the Delta State University junior varsity squad.Joe Adajo of Abuja, Nigeria; Jamarius Gray of Hattiesburg High, and Curtis Sangbarani of Aberdeen, Scotland, scored solo goals for the Wildcats, while PRCC''s fourth score came via a Trojan own goal.PRCC returns to action when MACJC non-division rival East Central visits Wednesday 5:30 p.m. (women) and 7:30 p.m. (men) contests, before opening its South Division schedule Saturday against Southwest Mississippi in Summit (women 1 p.m., men 3 p.m.).
